  "story": {
    "title": "The Theory of Success",
    "body": "In a familiar school, a student named Rafi had a single purpose in life: success. He believed in a simple theory that hard work and balance always bring results. One day, his teacher allowed students to propose ideas for a science project. Rafi arranged his work carefully and attended every class to understand the pattern of learning. At first, the challenge was huge, and he felt like tearing up his notes in frustration. But his teacher encouraged him to stay calm and continue. Rafi decided to grab every opportunity and not avoid difficulties. He contributed ideas, followed instructions, and balanced his time between study and rest. Slowly, his project improved. The result was announced, and Rafi achieved great success. Everyone in the community praised him. He realized that necessary effort, patience, and a clear purpose can change everything. Therefore, he promised to always work wisely in the future.",
